				<h2 class='post-title entry-title '  itemprop="headline" >	<a href='https://amgreatness.com/2020/06/02/nypd-police-union-pres-says-cops-are-being-used-as-pawns-told-to-stand-down-are-losing-the-city/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: NYPD Police Union Pres. Says Cops Are Being Used as &#8216;Pawns,&#8217; Told to &#8216;Stand Down,&#8217; Are &#8216;Losing the City&#8217;'>NYPD Police Union Pres. Says Cops Are Being Used as &#8216;Pawns,&#8217; Told to &#8216;Stand Down,&#8217; Are &#8216;Losing the City&#8217;			<span class='post-format-icon minor-meta'></span>	</a></h2>			
									
				<span class='post-meta-infos'><a href='https://amgreatness.com/author/debra-heine/' class='post-author-format-type'><span class='rounded-container'><img alt='Debra Heine' src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%2081%2081'%3E%3C/svg%3E" data-lazy-srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c849b6c5c9ff2f3532cf6f542e256c01?s=162&#038;d=blank&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-81 photo' height='81' width='81' data-lazy-src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c849b6c5c9ff2f3532cf6f542e256c01?s=81&#038;d=blank&#038;r=g" /><noscript><img alt='Debra Heine' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c849b6c5c9ff2f3532cf6f542e256c01?s=81&#038;d=blank&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c849b6c5c9ff2f3532cf6f542e256c01?s=162&#038;d=blank&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-81 photo' height='81' width='81' /></noscript><span class="iconfont" aria-hidden='true' data-av_icon='' data-av_iconfont='entypo-fontello'></span></span></a><span class="blog-author minor-meta">By <span class="entry-author-link" ><span class="vcard author"><span class="fn"><a href="https://amgreatness.com/author/debra-heine/" title="Posts by Debra Heine" rel="author">Debra Heine</a></span></span></span></span><span class='text-sep text-sep-date'> • </span><time class='date-container minor-meta updated' >June 2, 2020</time><span class='comment-container minor-meta'><a href="https://amgreatness.com/2020/06/02/nypd-police-union-pres-says-cops-are-being-used-as-pawns-told-to-stand-down-are-losing-the-city/#respond" class="comments-link" ><span class="dsq-postid" data-dsqidentifier="60967 https://amgreatness.com/?p=60967">0 Comments</span></a></span><span class='text-sep text-sep-comment'> | </span><span class="blog-categories minor-meta">in <a href="https://amgreatness.com/category/news/" rel="tag">News</a> <a href="https://amgreatness.com/homepage_placement/news/" rel="tag">News</a> </span><span class="text-sep text-sep-cat"></span></span></header><div class="entry-content"  itemprop="text" ><p>In <a href="https://www.facebook.com/sbanypd/posts/3016295705125288?__xts__[0]=68.ARB-_TRh4Ucrcs6E1BwYLtIKf-dDMD3deDiV4swCyupRMojxh2l1TzJuaprTquNnS5NHTX45bhzHtQz-l03CMcCGg02iDiBsDbrm-n4nOww_UPPEm22snpYj-3pVgSHT7Z3niBrzRGmB5-orayCrc0Dsxlxf7MMl2MWNK5x-1DJbSXVENacBtaMtcJq4XOuNoKw8XEF7bsOXINJyeiSBgQDDeCtLhf8T6bHUQ_VngiW6Zd378MioDbO24MsuLA-kG8Hfnu8buox9330odhASk4V5ISfoTUHsG_WmabM_BykKkaEN9yzJNVyIPWY8Ixvt1IItntrAQfPY9QT7_PxfIg&amp;__tn__=-R">an incredible letter</a> to rank and file officers Tuesday, the president of the NYPD Sergeants Benevolent Association lamented that law enforcement officers are &#8220;losing the city&#8221; because they are being &#8220;held back&#8221; and used as &#8220;pawns&#8221; by New York City&#8217;s leaders.</p>
<p>&#8220;I am being inundated with calls, text messages and emails pleading for help,&#8221; SBA President Ed Mullins wrote.</p>
<blockquote><p>Please know that I am reading each and every correspondence I receive. I want each of you to know that I am very much aware of everything that is occurring in our city. I know we are losing the city. We have no leadership, no direction, and no plan. I know you are being held back and used as pawns.</p></blockquote>
<p>Violent anarchists, opportunistic criminals and organized agitators have for the past week used the killing of George Floyd in Minneapolis as a pretext to to do massive economic damage to businesses in cities across the nation.</p>
<p>In recent days, the agitators have looted and rioted their way across New York City, leaving dozens of damaged restaurants, stores, and cafes in their wake, not to mention<a href="https://www.policeone.com/officer-safety/articles/over-30-cops-injured-300-arrested-during-nyc-riots-pFinLG8yQe5f5E9c/"> dozens of injured police officers.</a></p>
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true">
<p lang="en" dir="ltr">Hard to describe how rampant the looting was tonight in Midtown Manhattan and how lawless it was. Complete anarchy. Literally hundreds of stores up and down Broadway, Fifth Ave, Sixth Ave. Kids ruling the streets like it was a party. <a href="https://t.co/y9Ly1UD1WX">pic.twitter.com/y9Ly1UD1WX</a></p>
<p>&mdash; Rachel Olding (@rachelolding) <a href="https://twitter.com/rachelolding/status/1267663717082238976?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">June 2, 2020</a></p></blockquote>
<p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p>
<p>An antifa group in NYC posted on Twitter Saturday that the purpose of the ongoing mayhem is to &#8220;push the rebellion as far as possible.&#8221;</p>
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true">
<p lang="en" dir="ltr">&quot;The Base,&quot; an extremist antifa &quot;political center&quot; operating out of Brooklyn, makes it clear that the goal is to push the insurrection &quot;as far as possible.&quot; A threat is issued to all counter-revolutionaries, including liberals. <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/antifa?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#antifa</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/GeorgeFloyd?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#GeorgeFloyd</a> <a href="https://t.co/LN0sUllnon">pic.twitter.com/LN0sUllnon</a></p>
<p>&mdash; Andy Ngô (@MrAndyNgo) <a href="https://twitter.com/MrAndyNgo/status/1267964378139119616?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">June 2, 2020</a></p></blockquote>
<p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p>
<p>NYC&#8217;s Marxist Mayor Bill de Blasio refused on Tuesday to allow the National Guard to come in and protect the city, saying they are not trained for &#8220;these tense situations.&#8221;</p>
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true">
<p lang="en" dir="ltr">We do not need the National Guard to come into New York City. When outside armed forces come into communities, especially these intense situations they have not been trained for, that’s a dangerous scenario. We have 36,000 police officers who will keep this city safe. <a href="https://t.co/ZSYCxRQ5jv">pic.twitter.com/ZSYCxRQ5jv</a></p>
<p>&mdash; Mayor Bill de Blasio (@NYCMayor) <a href="https://twitter.com/NYCMayor/status/1267898885273518089?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">June 2, 2020</a></p></blockquote>
<p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p>
<p>Even after a poll showed that an <a href="https://americanpriority.com/news/silent-majority-poll-shows-american-voters-support-use-of-military-national-guard-in-riots/">overwhelming majority of Americans</a> support having the National Guard deployed to riot-torn cities, CNN&#8217;s Chris Cuomo continued gaslighting the American people about the &#8220;protests&#8221; tearing the communities apart. After attempting to blame the riots on &#8220;white supremacist infiltrators,&#8221; CNN appears to be back to trying to excuse the violence.</p>
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true">
<p lang="en" dir="ltr">A sweeping majority of *Democrats* want the National Guard in their cities tonight.</p>
<p>Meanwhile, <a href="https://twitter.com/ChrisCuomo?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@ChrisCuomo</a> proclaims that protests don’t need to be “polite and peaceful.”</p>
<p>What a seditious, virus-spreading thug.<a href="https://t.co/Y5fixx6Zcu">pic.twitter.com/Y5fixx6Zcu</a></p>
<p>&mdash; BDW (@BryanDeanWright) <a href="https://twitter.com/BryanDeanWright/status/1268029358188433408?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">June 3, 2020</a></p></blockquote>
<p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p>
<p>NYC cops were not feeling &#8220;polite of peaceful&#8221; themselves after De Blasio took the side of the rioters over an officer who had to draw his weapon Sunday night.</p>
<p>The Marxist mayor condemned the officer after seeing a partial video of the incident, calling it &#8220;absolutely unacceptable.”</p>
<p>Another video of the incident however shows a protester hitting a lieutenant on the back of his head with a brick before the officer unholstered his weapon. The SBA Twitter account tweeted out the video.</p>
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true">
